div.p:
Substantiating this claim, the Minister for Foreign Affairs has pointed out to me
                    that, according to the provisions of Article One, a Special Mission was named;
                    as established in Articles Two and Three the Mission contained the proper
                    elements, and was present in Tegucigalpa before the last day of December, 1917;
                    complying with Article Four every effort is claimed to have been made to prevent
                    any possible cause for disagreement.
